85
00:04:26,799 --> 00:04:27,734
-A judo club!?
-Judo.

86
00:04:28,501 --> 00:04:31,070
A judo club… I did judo too.

87
00:04:31,137 --> 00:04:32,705
I actually wanted to do sumo the most.

88
00:04:32,772 --> 00:04:35,008
But my school
had no dohyo, so I joined judo.

89
00:04:37,877 --> 00:04:41,981
This is my first time
at a chanko nabe place.

90
00:04:42,048 --> 00:04:43,783
By the way, what's chanko?

91
00:04:43,850 --> 00:04:48,087
Chanko is the general term

92
00:04:48,154 --> 00:04:50,790
for food that sumo wrestlers eat
at the sumo stable.

93
00:04:51,524 --> 00:04:56,529
Sumo wrestlers
train full-tilt from morning.

94
00:05:00,733 --> 00:05:05,238
Lower-ranked wrestlers cook
while the seniors train.

95
00:05:07,674 --> 00:05:11,744
The main hot pot among those dishes

96
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:14,681
is chanko nabe.

97
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:21,888
They pack the pot
with nutrients and ingredients.

98
00:05:23,523 --> 00:05:27,593
Each sumo stable has
its own method for simmering broth.

99
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:30,863
Are there different bases, like ramen?

100
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:31,864
There are.

101
00:05:31,931 --> 00:05:36,336
Shio, shoyu, and miso.

102
00:05:36,402 --> 00:05:39,072
These days,
there are all kinds of bases, right?

103
00:05:39,138 --> 00:05:42,875
Right.
There are spicy, stew-style ones too.

104
00:05:42,942 --> 00:05:45,945
There are so many kinds of chanko.
What do you recommend?

105
00:05:46,646 --> 00:05:50,650
Kokonoe chanko
packs the most ingredients.

106
00:05:50,717 --> 00:05:51,651
-With everything.
-Yes.

107
00:05:51,718 --> 00:05:53,286
KOKONOE CHANKO NABE

